      div(class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2")
        h1(style="text-align:center") Masks for All in Pakistan (#[a(href="www.maskbanao.com") www.maskbanao.com])
        br
        h3(style="text-align:center") Raising Pakistan's mask prevalence from zero to widespread.
        //h3(style="text-align:center") A Mask Creation and Wearing Campaign in Pakistan.
        //img(class="fit center-me", style="width:64%", src="images/maskbanao1.png")
        img(class="fit center-me", style="max-height: 45vh", src="images/ayesha-mask-1.jpg")
        br
        p MaskBanao is a project built by a small group of students aiming to bring Pakistan's mask-wearing prevalence from zero to widespread.  When none of Pakistan's 220 million people were wearing a mask, MaskBanao partnered with Pakistan's provincial governors and famous celebrities to promote universal mask wearing.
        p What started out as a Pakistani friend and I discussing COVID in a dorm room, grew to be a mask making and wearing campaign that included dozens of designers, artists, government officials, and web developers from Pakistan to the Philippines to Croatia. Our campaign talked to the governor of a Pakistani province containing 50 million people, created celebrity-backed mask videos that reached a hundred thousand, and delivered over 120,000 masks to citizens of Pakistan.
        p Our mission was to educate people all over Pakistan to save lives by creating masks at home. A simple mask can be made from a T-shirt. 
        // When we started, no one in Pakistan wore a mask. What started as a small idea grew into a team of over 35 students and professionals from 8 different countries.   
      div.row(style="margin-bottom: 0.5cm")
        div(class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2")
          img(class="fit center-me", src="images/omar.jpg")
        //div(class="col-lg-4 col-md-6")
