            div(class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2")
              strong Hadiqa Kiani is Pakistan's first female Goodwill ambassador to the United Nations. 
              span In this #[a(href="https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=233459321239553") video] produced with Maskbanao, she urges Pakistanis to wear masks.
        div(class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2" style="margin-top: 1cm")
        p Besides for celebrity advocacy, we also discussed COVID strategy with Pakistani governors. By reaching out to our distant connections, our small team arranged a meeting in mid-April 2020 with the governor of Pakistan's most populous province to advise him on coronavirus policy. We later worked with more government officials, including technology advisers to the Prime Minister of Pakistan.  The Pakistani government eventually issued a mask order during the first wave of the pandemic.
        p MaskBanao was featured in Pakistan's largest #[a(href="https://images.dawn.com/news/1185249") newspapers], including BBC.
        br
        strong Learn more about us at #[a(href="https://www.maskbanao.com") www.maskbanao.com].
        br
        br
        h3(class="center-text") Get Involved
        p MaskBanao is no longer active at the time of writing. However, if you would like to learn about similar, ongoing global initiatives, please email me #[a(href="mailto:timothyzchu@gmail.com") timothyzchu [at] gmail [dot] com] to have a friendly chat!
        br
